"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 18, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nao1705584403425.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nao1705584403425.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nao1705584403425.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hmr1665702852149\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Translation Tables\n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__p_d13667e1_d13668e1_d13669e1\">Translation tables are compiled sets of definitions that map platform-specific input and output codes to Uniface internal meta codes. All interaction with input and output devices is table-driven. This allows Uniface to work with a wide variety of devices without knowing the details for each one.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__p_d13670e1_d13671e1_d13672e1\">There are four types of translation table, which are classified as either keyboard translation tables, which handle input data streams from keyboards and databases, or as device translation tables, which handle output data streams to screens and printers.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Types of Translation Table</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n device translation tables\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to output device functions\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n Display\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to device display code\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n Printer\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to printer code\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n keyboard translation tables\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map input codes to Uniface logical function codes and meta characters\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n Keyboard\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map keyboard codes to Uniface logical function codes and meta characters\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__1\">\n DBMS\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"hmr1665702852149__table_d1400e1_d1401e1_d1402e1__entry__2\">\n Map meta code to meta code. DBMS translation tables provide database translation capability for fields in form components.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hmr1665702852149__p_d13673e1_d13674e1_d13675e1\">For every system supported, Uniface supplies a set of translation tables in the Dynamic Object Library <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.uar</span>. These should be sufficient in most cases. If the translation table you require is not present, you can define your own. It is usually much easier to copy an existing table and modify it, than to define an entirely new one yourself. The translation table definitions belong to the USYS library and are available in <span class=\"ph filepath\">libdvc.usys.xml</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">libktt.usys.xml</span>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aud1665702670477.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Meta Character Sets</a><p>Meta character sets are used for translating installable character sets and defining translation tables. In earlier versions of Uniface, meta character sets were used as internal character sets instead of Unicode.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5829815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5829815\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Translation Tables Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 18, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Translation Tables To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables. Translation tables are compiled sets of definitions that map platform-specific input and output codes to Uniface internal meta codes. All interaction with input and output devices is table-driven. This allows Uniface to work with a wide variety of devices without knowing the details for each one. There are four types of translation table, which are classified as either keyboard translation tables, which handle input data streams from keyboards and databases, or as device translation tables, which handle output data streams to screens and printers. Table 1. Types of Translation Table Type Description device translation tables Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to output device functions Display Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to device display code Printer Map Uniface logical functions and meta characters to printer code keyboard translation tables Map input codes to Uniface logical function codes and meta characters Keyboard Map keyboard codes to Uniface logical function codes and meta characters DBMS Map meta code to meta code. DBMS translation tables provide database translation capability for fields in form components. For every system supported, Uniface supplies a set of translation tables in the Dynamic Object Library usys.uar . These should be sufficient in most cases. If the translation table you require is not present, you can define your own. It is usually much easier to copy an existing table and modify it, than to define an entirely new one yourself. The translation table definitions belong to the USYS library and are available in libdvc.usys.xml and libktt.usys.xml . Related Links Meta Character Sets Meta character sets are used for translating installable character sets and defining translation tables. In earlier versions of Uniface, meta character sets were used as internal character sets instead of Unicode. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}